{
  "final_answer": "## AI Segment's Contribution to the Consolidated GAAP-to-Adjusted-EBITDA Bridge (FY2025)\n\n### Answer: ~44.42%\n\nThe AI segment contributed approximately **$5,118 million** of the **$11,521 million** total consolidated adjustment from Net Loss to Adjusted EBITDA in FY2025, equal to **~44.42%** of the total consolidated bridge.\n\n---\n\n### Step 1 — Total Consolidated GAAP-to-Adjusted-EBITDA Bridge (FY2025)\n\nSource: SpaceX S-1 (filed May 20, 2026), consolidated reconciliation. Figures reflect the retrospectively recast consolidated entity (including xAI and X Holdings).\n\n| Line Item | FY2025 ($M) |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| Net income (loss) | (4,937) |\n| Depreciation and amortization | 6,701 |\n| Share-based compensation | 1,947 |\n| Restructuring charges | 487 |\n| Impairments | 38 |\n| Interest expense | 1,945 |\n| Interest income | (492) |\n| Other (income) expense, net | 177 |\n| Provision for (benefit from) income taxes | 718 |\n| **Adjusted EBITDA** | **6,584** |\n\n**Total consolidated adjustment** = $6,584 − (−$4,937) = **$11,521M**\n(Verified: sum of all individual add-backs = $6,701 + $1,947 + $487 + $38 + $1,945 − $492 + $177 + $718 = $11,521M ✓)\n\n---\n\n### Step 2 — AI Segment's Contribution to the Bridge (FY2025)\n\nSource: SpaceX S-1, segment-level reconciliation of Income (loss) from operations to Segment Adjusted EBITDA.\n\n| AI Segment Line Item | FY2025 ($M) |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| Income (loss) from operations | (6,355) |\n| Depreciation and amortization | 3,568 |\n| Share-based compensation | 1,063 |\n| Restructuring charges | 487 |\n| Impairment | — |\n| **Segment Adjusted EBITDA** | **(1,237)** |\n\n**AI segment adjustment** = (−$1,237) − (−$6,355) = **$5,118M**\n(Verified: $3,568 + $1,063 + $487 + $0 = $5,118M ✓)\n\n---\n\n### Step 3 — AI Segment Contribution as % of Total Consolidated Adjustment\n\n$$\\frac{\\$5{,}118\\text{M}}{\\$11{,}521\\text{M}} = 0.4442 \\approx \\mathbf{44.42\\%}$$\n\n### Component Breakdown of AI's Contribution\n\n| AI Adjustment Component | $M | % of Total Consolidated Adjustment |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| Depreciation and amortization | 3,568 | 30.97% |\n| Share-based compensation | 1,063 | 9.23% |\n| Restructuring charges | 487 | 4.23% |\n| Impairment | 0 | 0.00% |\n| **Total AI segment contribution** | **5,118** | **44.42%** |\n\n---\n\n### Context and Observations\n\n- The AI segment is the single largest contributor to the consolidated GAAP-to-Adjusted-EBITDA bridge, despite generating a Segment Adjusted EBITDA loss of $(1,237)M. This is because the segment's GAAP operating loss of $(6,355)M is substantially reduced by large non-cash and one-time add-backs (notably $3,568M of D&A and $1,063M of SBC, plus the entire $487M of consolidated restructuring charges).\n- The AI segment alone accounts for ~53% of consolidated D&A ($3,568M / $6,701M) and ~55% of consolidated SBC ($1,063M / $1,947M), and 100% of consolidated restructuring charges.\n- The remaining ~55.58% of the consolidated bridge comes from: the Space segment (~$1,310M, ~11.37%), the Connectivity segment (~$2,745M, ~23.83%), and corporate/non-segment items below the operating line (interest, taxes, other — ~$2,348M, ~20.38%).\n- All figures reflect the recast consolidated entity under common-control accounting (xAI merged Feb 2, 2026; X Holdings merged into xAI March 28, 2025); no period reflects standalone SpaceX operations exclusively.\n\n---\n\n{\n  \"sources\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm\",\n      \"name\": \"SpaceX S-1 Registration Statement (filed May 20, 2026) — Consolidated and Segment Adjusted EBITDA Reconciliations, FY2025\"\n    }\n  ]\n}",
